# Anti-vibecoding discipline

## File size
- Hard ceiling 500 lines. Soft target 300. Split when over.
- One default-exported component per file (route specials excepted).
- Functions ≤30 lines target. Max 3 positional parameters — switch to an
  options object after 3.

## Single responsibility
- Each module has ONE responsibility named in a one-line file header comment.
- Database layer returns `{ data, error }` tuples; service layer maps to
  domain results; UI layer renders. Never mix layers.
- Three-layer mental model: routes (thin HTTP/RSC) → services (business logic)
  → repositories (data access). Service methods accept and return domain
  models, never raw rows.

## Naming
- Files: kebab-case (`user-profile-card.tsx`, `format-date.ts`).
- React components: PascalCase identifier.
- Functions/variables: camelCase. Booleans: `is*`, `has*`, `should*`, `can*`.
- Event props: `onX`. Implementations: `handleX`.
- Constants/env: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE.
- Types/interfaces: PascalCase, no `I` prefix. Zod schemas: `XSchema`.

## Magic numbers and strings
- No magic numbers/strings in business logic. Extract to named const in
  `lib/constants.ts` or a closer scope with a comment explaining meaning.
- Status/kind values are union literal types defined once in `types/index.ts`.

## Composition over flags
- React components use `children` and named `ReactNode` slots over boolean
  toggles and content arrays. Booleans only for real state (disabled, loading,
  selected). When behavior diverges, use a discriminated union with a literal
  `kind` prop.
- Functions: no flag parameters that switch logic. If multiple modes are
  needed, write multiple functions or split into a small object dispatch.

## Hooks and performance
- Hooks called unconditionally at the top.
- Group correlated state in `useReducer` rather than fanning out `useState`.
- Extract any hook combo used 2+ times into a custom `useX` returning a stable
  object/2-tuple.
- `useEffect` synchronizes with external systems only. Derived state is
  computed inline or via `useMemo`.
- `useMemo`/`useCallback` ONLY when downstream `React.memo` or a hook deps
  array requires a stable reference, OR computation is measurably expensive.
  Never reflexively.
- Stable data-derived list keys; never index keys when items can reorder.

## Error handling
- Validate inputs and preconditions at the top (guard clauses). Happy path last.
  Early returns, not nested conditionals.
- Never swallow errors. Either handle (user-facing feedback) or re-throw with
  context.
- NO FALLBACKS that hide root causes. Add a fallback only if the user explicitly asks.
- Error messages include enough context to debug (request params, response
  body, status codes). No generic "something went wrong".

## Imports and dependencies
- Group built-in → external → internal (`@/`) → parent → sibling → index → object
  → type. Sort alphabetically.
- Absolute imports from `@/`. Never relative `../../...`.
- Avoid circular dependencies.

## Tooling backstop (rules ≠ enforcement)
- Cursor rules are documentation; ESLint, `tsc --noEmit`, and CI are enforcement.
- After implementing changes: run `npm run lint` and `npm run build`
  (do not start the dev server).
- `npm run build` MUST pass before every git commit.
